nfts.name: send/receive #5846
nfts.description:
*send/receive* is a conceptual artwork that celebrates the digital art community and the technology that connects us. It is a fully on-chain, highly participatory system in which every collector becomes a co-creator contributing their presence, energy, and intention to a network of interdependent artworks running on Ethereum.

Each artwork is alive to the global state of the network. Block by block, the balance between "sending" and "receiving" across all tokens determines what each piece displays. As collectors change their settings, the entire network shifts in real time.

Collectors begin by creating a 64×64 pixel character, a personal sprite, to represent themselves on the network. Optionally, they can compose a simple four-track audio tune to accompany their sprite. This can be done through the Art Blocks interface, which records and submits the creation directly to the blockchain, or through the fully on-chain editors embedded in the artwork itself, allowing collectors to generate a data string and manually update their token via Etherscan.

By default, each token starts in a neutral state. If a sprite has been added, the artwork displays it as a static image. From there, collectors choose how they want to participate: send, receive, or both.

These choices shape the global system. When more tokens are sending, the receiving tokens display incoming sprites more rapidly. When more tokens choose to receive, the senders are distributed across the network at a slower pace. Each token expresses its role visually:
* Receive mode: a continuous flow of incoming sprites, presented in one of four styles assigned at mint (grid, column, fall, or bounce).
* Send mode: your sprite remains centered, occasionally pulsing outward as it broadcasts.
* Send + Receive: your token displays its receive style with a subtle pulsing border to indicate that it is also sending.

Collectors are invited to adjust their token's setting as their mood changes to give, to take, or to hold both impulses at once. The more you take, the less others receive. The less you take, the more others receive. The system reflects these choices instantly, on-chain, creating an ever-shifting portrait of community intention.

The project was inspired by how people in our community often say "sending thoughts and prayers" to express support, or "send your thoughts and prayers" when they need encouragement. As someone who is not religious, I wanted to explore the underlying sentiment without invoking prayer directly to create a way for us to express care, attention, and presence through the medium of networked art.

Empathy is the foundation of this work. In a world that increasingly questions its value, I believe empathy is essential not only for navigating our digital lives, but for understanding each other at all. Taking a moment to step into someone else's shoes can illuminate motivations, reduce friction, and help us meet each other with generosity. send/receive is an experiment in using on-chain art to make that exchange visible, felt, and shared.

nfts.name: Diggly Collects All #219
nfts.description:
# ✨ Meet Diggly Collects All! ✨

Diggly Collects All is a fully on-chain generative art project that transforms the timeless joy of discovery and curation into a creative activity on the blockchain.
The token holder plays the role of Diggly - an imaginary digging creature who scours the land in search of rare finds. Upon gathering an assortment of natural treasures, Diggly arranges them into a fancy collection of items on a shelf to display to the world.

# A World Waiting Just For You

Part simulation, part artwork, each token represents a completely unique and deterministic world full of unexpected finds and creative exploration. Using the Post Parameters feature on the Art Blocks platform, the player’s assembled collection becomes designated as the ownership-defining token artwork.

Diggly Collects All is more than a standard artwork edition—it is a celebration of searching, finding, arranging, and sharing. It invites every holder to become an explorer, to dig through the private corner of their deterministic world, and to leave a permanent, personal mark on the blockchain.

nfts.name: Vanishing Of The Genuine: Holy Skull Of God
nfts.description:
"Holy Skull of God" is a symbolic representation of a model of deer, springbok, blesbok, pig and cow bones.  It was trained and generated from a Stable Diffusion LoRA model composed of photography of animal bones.   It fits into the simulation stage of representation. This art has more realistic twin that was captured on analog film called "Sky Face" and "Unholy Skull Of God".

"Bones: Vanishing of the Genuine" explores the beauty of bone and sky in life, death and simulation using analog film photography and AI as inspired by Georgia O'Keeffe's bones in the New Mexico sky and Jean Baudrillard's concept of hyperreality.  

Bård examines the authenticity of artifacts by juxtaposing bones, their photographs and AI generated images, questioning the transition from reality to symbol to simulation to simulacra.  Through the stages of an AI simulation and process a new reality is constructed. 

Process

The process to create Bones was to gather animal bones from ethical suppliers, but one key deer skull was found on the side of the road.  These bones were photographed with analog film cameras against the backdrop of the sky. The developed film was scanned and Photoshop was used to remove the filament holding the bone up.  The photos were used to train multiple GAN and Stable diffusion models. 

The process illustrates the progression of the real bone into a physical representation on film, then digitized into more symbolic systems. The model training turned the images of the bones into a simulation that can recreate any sort of bone and the background of the sky.  A final stage for a rare few tokens was to image the digital Ai image back onto analog film. These images tip into simulacra where the image no longer refers back to any real or even symbolic bone but exists in a self-referential loop of images.

The art of "Bones" fall into four stages of representation. 
It begins with the real physical bone - Reality
First the film photograph represents the symbol, a reflection of reality - Symbol
Second the film is digitized and edited to remove fishing line hanging bone in the sky - Distorted Symbol
Third the AI images generated from the model - Simulation Absence Of Reality
Fourth the AI images processed on film and model trained from first order model. A self-referential entity, creating a hyperreal world where the distinction between reality and simulation is obliterated - Simulacra

It is of note that the models were not completely trained on film photos. About 2,000 photos were created using a Olympus Pen EE-3, Mini Diana, Nikon A8008 and iPhone 12.  Around 1,500 were film and the rest were digital photos from the iPhone and the Dehancer app emulated Kodak Gold Film.

RIGHTS & LICENSE:
The NFT collector receives:
Non-exclusive Display rights (private/public)
Permission to create remixes and Ai model training with attribution

Artist retains reproduction rights, commercial licensing, reproduction rights
Artist may produce limited edition prints of this piece
Copyright 2024 Bard Ionson LLC

nfts.name: Vanishing Of The Genuine: Bone, Cloud, Flag
nfts.description:
In the sky forms appear, a flag of cloud turns to bone. Modern simulation hyperreality where the temporal is made eternal in the model of artificial intelligence. In this new culture we question what is real and what is simulated.

"Bone, Cloud, Flag" is a simulation of a model of film and digital photos of deer, springbok, blesbok, pig and cow bones with sky, night and flags in the background.  It was trained and generated from a StyleGAN 2 model using film and digital photographs taken by the artist.

"Vanishing of the Genuine" explores the beauty of bone and sky in life, death and simulation using analog film photography and AI as inspired by Georgia O'Keeffe's bones in the New Mexico sky and Jean Baudrillard's concept of hyperreality.  

The beauty of the bone floating in the sky with clouds and trees exposes the human perception of the world and the alterations of technology in the form of artificial intelligence. But these bones and the Ai model hold the promise of immortality, the bone outlasts death and perhaps we hope the simulation / simulacra of our creation will also be immortal. 

Bård examines the authenticity of artifacts by juxtaposing bones, their photographs and AI generated images, questioning the transition from reality to symbol to simulation to simulacra.  Through the stages of an AI simulation and process a new reality is constructed. 

Process

The process to create Bones was to gather animal bones from ethical suppliers, but one key deer skull was found on the side of the road.  These bones were photographed with analog film cameras against the backdrop of the sky. The developed film was scanned and Photoshop was used to remove the filament holding the bone up.  The photos were used to train multiple GAN and Stable diffusion models. 

The process illustrates the progression of the real bone into a physical representation on film, then digitized into more symbolic systems. The model training turned the images of the bones into a simulation that can recreate any sort of bone and the background of the sky. 

It is of note that the models were not completely trained on film photos. About 1,500 photos were created using analog film of  Olympus Pen EE-3, Mini Diana and Nikon A8008 .  Around 500 were digital photos from an iPhone 12 and the Dehancer app emulated Kodak Gold Film.

nfts.name: Extinction (Cult Of CryptoArt version)
nfts.description:
The Cult Of Crypto Art Version which appeared at NFC Summit 2025 Lisbon in the Cult Of Crypto Art exhibition

What is real and what will be real tomorrow?

Modern simulation hyperreality simulacra via Ai in the life cycle of the cultures of nations being reorganized by technology and artificial intelligence.

"Extinction" is a simulation of a model of film and digital photos of deer, springbok, blesbok, pig and cow bones with the US flag and the sky in the background.  It was trained and generated from a StyleGAN 2 model using photographs taken by the artist.

"Vanishing of the Genuine" explores the beauty of bone and sky in life, death and simulation using analog film photography and AI as inspired by Georgia O'Keeffe's bones in the New Mexico sky and Jean Baudrillard's concept of hyperreality.  

The beauty of the bone floating in the sky with clouds and trees exposes the human perception of the world and the alterations of technology in the form of artificial intelligence. But these bones and the Ai model hold the promise of immortality, the bone outlasts death and perhaps we hope the simulation / simulacra of our creation will also be immortal. 

Bård examines the authenticity of artifacts by juxtaposing bones, their photographs and AI generated images, questioning the transition from reality to symbol to simulation to simulacra.  Through the stages of an AI simulation and process a new reality is constructed. 

Process

The process to create Bones was to gather animal bones from ethical suppliers, but one key deer skull was found on the side of the road.  These bones were photographed with analog film cameras against the backdrop of the sky. The developed film was scanned and Photoshop was used to remove the filament holding the bone up.  The photos were used to train multiple GAN and Stable diffusion models. 

The process illustrates the progression of the real bone into a physical representation on film, then digitized into more symbolic systems. The model training turned the images of the bones into a simulation that can recreate any sort of bone and the background of the sky.  A final stage for a rare few tokens was to image the digital Ai image back onto analog film. These images tip into simulacra where the image no longer refers back to any real or even symbolic bone but exists in a self-referential loop of images.

The art of "Bones" fall into four stages of representation. 
It begins with the real physical bone - Reality
First the film photograph represents the symbol, a reflection of reality - Symbol
Second the film is digitized and edited to remove fishing line hanging bone in the sky - Distorted Symbol
Third the AI images generated from the model - Simulation Absence Of Reality
Fourth the AI images processed on film and model trained from first order model. A self-referential entity, creating a hyperreal world where the distinction between reality and simulation is obliterated - Simulacra

It is of note that the models were not completely trained on film photos. About 1,500 photos were created using analog film of  Olympus Pen EE-3, Mini Diana and Nikon A8008 .  Around 500 were digital photos from an iPhone 12 and the Dehancer app emulated Kodak Gold Film.

nfts.name: Infinite Garden: 53411 Flowers
nfts.description:
Infinite Garden, 2025
Leander Herzog

https://www.infinite-garden.xyz/3650

Nguyen Wahed presents Infinite Garden, a solo exhibition by Leander Herzog in New York. For two months, beginning March 17, the standalone installation transforms the concept of digital materiality through an ever-shifting botanical ecosystem on blockchain where no single moment repeats itself. Herzog's new work employs blockchain affordances as a creative medium, building a space where collectors become active participants in the cultivation of living digital flora - works conceived collectively through a smart contract. Each element exists in a state of perpetual evolution, responding to temporal conditions including diurnal cycles and seasonal progressions.
Flowers can be minted through Shape. They may be combined, creating personal arrangements in one’s garden that evolve over time. Flowers can be gifted to other collectors and merged to a new garden. OpenSea facilitates the acquisition of flowers on secondary needed to diversify existing gardens.
Infinite Garden invites the audience to root for blockchain not merely as a transactional framework but as an expressive medium with distinct properties for generative art. Presented in partnership with Shape, and supported by OpenSea. 50% of the proceeds are donated to Protocol Guild, a collective funding mechanism for Ethereum core protocol maintainers.

nfts.name: Power Corrupts Power 11: This is going to be great television.
nfts.description:
The King Of America:
They didn’t respect Obama. They respect me. Let me tell you, Putin went through a hell of a lot with me. He went through a phony witch hunt ... All I can say is this. He might have broken deals with Obama and Bush, and he might have broken them with Biden. He did, maybe. Maybe he did. I don’t know what happened, but he didn’t break them with me. He wants to make a deal. I don’t know if you can make a deal.”

nfts.name: SIXTEEN X NINE | BHM 2025
nfts.description:
A special edition of the 16:9 digital zine, preserving culture on-chain and celebrating African American innovation and global influence. This token acts as a mint-to-redeem mechanism—holders who mint it will be eligible to claim the zine, a collectible artifact of Black excellence and creativity.

16:9 – Black History & Innovation Edition

In celebration of Black History Month, this special edition of the 16:9 digital zine preserves culture on-chain, spotlighting African American innovation and global influence. As a mint-to-redeem mechanism, this NFT serves as the gateway to claiming an exclusive zine—an artifact that honours Black excellence, creativity, and the indelible mark left on history and the future.

Preserving Culture On-Chain

The blockchain is more than a technology; it’s a ledger of truth, a space where history can be recorded, owned, and passed down without alteration. In the spirit of preservation, 16:9 – Black History & Innovation Edition ensures that the contributions of Black visionaries—past, present, and future—remain documented, immutable, and accessible. This edition captures the essence of African American ingenuity across various disciplines, from science and technology to music, literature, and the arts.

By leveraging blockchain’s permanence, we are reclaiming the narrative, ensuring that Black stories are remembered and owned by those who engage with and contribute to them. The zine itself exists as a collectable artifact, marking a new way to experience and archive culture in a decentralised world.

Innovation & Influence

Black history is a history of innovation. From the scientific breakthroughs of George Washington Carver and Katherine Johnson to the artistic revolutions led by Jean-Michel Basquiat and Octavia Butler, African American ingenuity has shaped global culture in profound ways. Hip-hop, jazz, and rock & roll—genres birthed from Black communities—continue to define music worldwide. Fashion, film, and literature shaped by Black creators influence industries on a global scale.

This edition of 16:9 curates a selection of these groundbreaking moments, paying homage to those who have pushed boundaries, rewritten rules, and built legacies despite systemic barriers. It also recognizes the modern-day innovators—technologists, digital artists, and cultural curators—who continue to shape the future.

The Mint-to-Redeem Mechanism

16:9 – Black History & Innovation Edition introduces a unique mint-to-redeem experience. By minting this token, holders gain eligibility to claim the digital zine, securing a piece of history on-chain. This mechanism not only reinforces the collectible nature of the zine but also offers an interactive way to engage with cultural preservation in Web3.

Rather than simply consuming content, minters become part of a decentralized archival process, contributing to the movement of Black storytelling in the digital space. The zine isn’t just a publication; it’s a testament to ownership, participation, and the continued evolution of Black creativity in a technological age.

A Living Archive of Black Excellence

This release of 16:9 serves as a reminder that Black history is not confined to the past—it’s a continuous force shaping the present and the future. Through blockchain technology, we are carving out new spaces where Black narratives are protected, celebrated, and valued.

As we honor the greats who paved the way, we also acknowledge the creators, thinkers, and builders who are defining what’s next. This zine stands as both a tribute and a tool—an artifact that ensures Black stories remain in our hands, on our terms, for generations to come.

Mint, claim, and preserve. Black history is innovation, and innovation is forever.

nfts.name: Noctilucent Memento #188
nfts.description:
Noctilucent Mementi is a generative chronicle that encapsulates 5 years of Martin Lukas Ostachowski's travels and work with clouds in cryptoart. Each artwork is a location-specific memento, forming a visual timeline of the artist's development, milestones and travels between 2018 and 2023, spanning 4 continents and 11 countries.  The term 'noctilucent', means 'luminous in the dark' and references high, invisible clouds. 'Mementi' represents the artist's curated visual memories. In MLO's words, "Noctilucent clouds are invisible memories, glowing when revisited." For MLO, clouds serve as a medium for speaking about the way that we transform and preserve intangible presences, both through personal memory and through digital wallets. In this, his first serial collection, MLO celebrates 5 years of artistic evolution since the creation of his first cloud artwork in September 2018.

Over the last 5 years, MLO has come to be known as "the cloud artist." He began tokenizing his art in June 2018, and has since become a formative figure in the cryptoart movement, making fundamental contributions to the cultural understanding of the medium. His early works use geometric minimalism and artistic data visualization to investigate and educate about the potential meanings of blockchains and tokens. With the piece "Cloud Seed Phrase Visualization" (September 2018), he arrived at a mode of translating data into metaphor that has since become the spine of his practice. In his words, "I find the analogy to clouds particularly intriguing, as we store only the rights to assets in our digital wallets while the actual digital assets remain permanently on the blockchain; the digital assets therefore remain intangible much like clouds in the sky." 

Clouds have personal weight for MLO as someone whose life has been defined by movement and transition. Born in Poland, raised in Germany, emigrated to Canada, and traveling constantly, he has lived in more than 33 different places through the years. For him, clouds are both an emblem of transience and a constant companion. In MLO's art, the distributed nodes that constitute a blockchain become a symbol of hope. This living cloud maintained by shared belief harbors the possibility of continuity for an individual identity through the fragile impermanence of physical locations. 

An illustrated break-down of the series' influences, underlying references and numerology can be found [here.](https://mlo.art/news/blog-posts/new-collection-noctilucent-mementi/)

A Sovrn Curated release.

nfts.name: Drawings for a Monument #82
nfts.description:
Drawings for a Monument is a generative series exploring the development of a minimalist monument to Art Blocks. Each drawing pays tribute to a different project from the Curated collection, examining its color expression within a linear framework. The algorithm translates the chromatic identity of each Curated project into hand-drawn geometric studies with pencil guidelines, painted rectangles, and black outlines.

In addition to being a creative endeavor, Drawings for a Monument is a personal reflection on my role at Art Blocks and the opportunities I've had to work with other generative artists on the platform. The drawings are equal parts technical investigation and emotional introspection as a way to more fully understand my history with Art Blocks over the last five years.

Drawings for a Monument also marks a full circle moment in my own artistic career, connecting the digital techniques I use today with where I started as an artist – as a painter working with traditional materials. The digital outputs replicate how I work by hand, using rulers and flat brushes for precision and methodically mixing colors from a core set of paints.

In the end, the full series of drawings becomes the monument itself. Together, they form both a personal archive and a collective tribute to the first five years of Art Blocks and its Curated collection.

nfts.name: Friendship Bracelets #38772
nfts.description:
Since founding Art Blocks in 2020, artist Erick Calderon (a.k.a. Snowfro) has been intrigued by the idea of representing digital artwork in the physical world in the form of an ephemeral physical object with meaning, but with no inherent value. 

Donald Judd has long been an inspiration for Art Blocks. One aspect we admire most about Judd’s artistic practice is the elegance of design he effortlessly paired with the accessibility of materials that could be found at a hardware store. With Judd as inspiration, we hatched a plan to create a unique generative art friendship bracelet that includes instructions to make, in minutes, a simple bracelet using a few dollars’ worth of embroidery floss. Donald Judd believed that what surrounds us in our day-to-day life is already so beautiful, and that ultimately the experience of creating art is as important as owning it.

Erick was incredibly excited to collaborate with renowned artist Alexis André (a.k.a. MacTuitui) to bring generative art and ephemeral physical objects together in the form of friendship bracelets. Conceptualized by Erick and aesthetically and programmatically designed by Alexis, this project pairs creative coding with a beautiful spectrum of embroidery floss colors. The project was a true team effort, as each member of the Art Blocks team designed and named their own color palette!

The project is a token of our appreciation to the creators, makers, builders, and collectors who have all contributed to making the Art Blocks community what it is today. Participating in this project is a signal, both online and IRL, that you’re a participant in this evolution of art + community. You are pushing the best ideas forward. You are the reason all of these imaginative projects come to life. Our community is what makes all of this possible. So, to say it plainly, we appreciate you, and we hope that you’ll accept this bracelet as a token of our special friendship!

The owner of any wallet with an Art Blocks piece at the time of snapshot (October 26, 2022, at 3pm US Central time) is eligible to claim two mints from this special generative art project. We would love to see you keep one bracelet and share your love for generative art by gifting your second mint! These mints are free to claim (you pay only the gas) and exist on L1 Ethereum. Please note that we may in the future release additional modified iterations of the Friendship Bracelets project, ideally on an L2 scaling solution, that may substantially increase the total supply of tokens related to the project, with the intent of being a more accessible entry point to a larger audience. But this version is what we're here to celebrate today, and this gift is for you in gratitude for your support along the way. Please enjoy this token of our friendship and explore the wonderful artwork created by Alexis André. Then, let's all make bracelets together! 

Warmly,
Alexis + Erick + the Art Blocks team



The claim window expires on January 10, 2023, at noon US Central time.

Click into the Display Notes for information about making your bracelet.

nfts.description:
Who The Frank Is This? is a limited collection of 333 unique 1/1 digital artworks, each one featuring Benjamin Franklin reimagined by the artist, created by AI and finalized by you.

At its core, this is a visual rebellion against traditional value systems. The artwork disrupts the authority of fiat by transforming the iconic $100 bill into a canvas for satire, pop culture, and digital identity. It blends the raw energy of street art with the decentralized spirit of Web3, remixing money into meme, myth, and meaning. They won’t be spent — they’ll be remembered.

Each piece is a collaboration between collector, machine, and the artist, captured on a dollar bill that was never meant to exist. From superheroes to saints, revolutionaries to absurdist icons, no two Franklins are alike — and no word can be used twice.

This is not just a mint — it's a creative experiment in identity, ownership, and language.
It all begins with a word which then becomes a prompt that generates your Franklin.
And once you mint it, it’s gone from the matrix forever.

The result is a collection as absurd, human, and unpredictable as all of us participating in its creation.

Once it’s minted, it’s yours.

Once it’s yours, it’s history.

So choose your word — and leave your mark.

nfts.name: Broken Dreams #70
nfts.description:
**Broken Dreams · TIMED EDITION**  
Available until October 31st, then never again.

The work will be exhibited in Barcelona at the Responsive Dreams Festival, and in Marfa during Art Blocks Weekend 2025. Once the show closes, so does the edition.  
  
- - -  
\
**Broken Dreams** explores the fragility of dreams.

In the fractured world we live in, dreams can be interrupted, even broken, yet they may remain alive if we hold on to them.

As they shift and change, they can surprise us in new forms, sparking joy, fueling imagination, pushing us to reach new heights, or returning as colorful memories that make us smile.  
\
**On-chain Evolution**  
Leveraging Art Blocks’ PostParams, Broken Dreams taps directly into Ethereum’s block data, allowing each dream to evolve in sync with the living network it inhabits. With each new block, the dream changes almost imperceptibly. Over time, these subtle transformations accumulate, reshaping the dream in a continuous evolution.  
\
**Triangular Color Sampling Technique**  
For the colors of this piece, I developed a system that generates thousands of unique and harmonious tones from a single palette.

First, a base layer is created, where the colors of the palette flow in an organic pattern. On top of this, each triangle samples five key points: the center, the three vertices, and the midpoint of its longest side. The algorithm calculates an average of these values to define the triangle’s final color.

In this way, each shape acquires a unique nuance, always derived from the same palette — infinite variations held together by a common harmony.  
\
⎻ ⎻ ⎻

**Keys:**  
[S] – Save image. 

[V] – Save 15-second video. 

[L] – Toggle cutting axis lines visibility. 

[R] – Disable Forecast owners Easter egg.

**Prints:**  
Prints will be available for Broken Dreams owners. A small collection of OOB outputs will also be available. For more details, [visit this link](https://www.mlarino.com/work/broken-dreams "order prints").

nfts.name: Seadragons #335
nfts.description:
"Seadragons" is a generative catalogue of imaginary sea creatures from Syngnathidae family. Each seadragon belongs to one of the real Weedy, Leafy or Ribboned species, while the patterns and the small leaf-like appendages are an artistic interpretation. The dragons are rendered in real-time allowing you to watch them slowly drifting in the water or moving your mouse to nudge them slightly.

This project is a continuation of my long term fascination with using code to recreate forms and patterns occurring in nature. By using a range of non-photorealistic rendering techniques I strive to document those explorations as if they were actual sketches, posters or biological illustrations of the encountered specimens. Algorithmic variations of their patterns, sizes, colors, poses, complexity and surrounding seaweed present in each artwork are only a minor drop compared to the diversity observed in natural environments. 

15% of profits will be donated to oceana.org for protecting and restoring the world’s oceans on a global scale. Another 10% will be donated to givewell.org.

nfts.name: Cyberfire
nfts.description:
A spectrum of incandescence, this grid weaves together fragments of luminosity and shadow. Each segment, a fleeting impression of warmth, coalesces into a complex narrative of light's evolution through an algorithm's eye, capturing the elusive dance of flames in a perpetual state of change.
Channeling the fire myths of the world, Prometheus, the Phoenix, the gods of the sun and flame. A story of technology brought to humans; to myths of destruction and rebirth. To be immortal; to be a god; it is always a paradox of fire and technology. The morality of the fire is always in question but we desire it and fear it. And yet it has changed us, we have learned so much since we first touched fire. We used it to destroy the wood, smelt the metal and build the chip. And now we teach and show the fire what we know; what we create and our reflection is there telling us our faults. The GAN is but a single neuron in a blazing star; a greater fire is coming.

To be immortal; to be a god; it is always a paradox of fire and technology. The morality of the fire is always in question but we desire it and fear it. And yet it has changed us, we have learned so much since we first touched fire. We used it to destroy the wood, smelt the metal and build the chip. And now we teach and show the fire what we know; what we create and our reflection is there telling us our faults. The GAN is but a single neuron in a blazing star; a greater fire is coming.

nfts.name: Meta-SPAM
nfts.description:
A SPAM performance in virtual reality. A meme of meaning, an energy source preserved in a packable stackable can to fight a war or two or three. The countries where SPAM performed became fused with their cultural cuisine. 

Upload the video to a platform that supports 360 video or to your VR Goggles and enjoy the performance and listen to that slurp as it slides out of the can.

A hand with a gold ring reaches down and holds a can of SPAM. A can with its distinctive gold can with blue label with the word SPAM in bold yellow.  With a second hand the artist pulls the ring tap slowly upwards. The hand grabs the can. An old CRT TV rests in the background. The can moves upward and upside down. The hand shakes the can again and again. Now the performance goes into slow motion. The edge of the can is seen at the top of the screen.The slab of SPAM slowly slides out, growing larger with its fall to the plate. It bounces slightly on the beige plate.

nfts.name: Pelvic Bone Moon
nfts.description: We carve out an on-chain Cabinet to give eternal life to the dead presences that Isa Kost has carried through the years. Isa's practice is defined by a deep connection with death, a self-archeology where finding speaks to what is lost. - "The journey became clear to me when, drawing the ficus leaf, the memory of my father caring for a ficus plant in our house when I was a child arose. So did the sun spider, found through my childhood desire to visit the pyramids in Egypt. And the scent of the gardenia, which enveloped me for days in my room in Mexico, collected in a small bouquet given to me by a dear friend." - Building a Wunderkammer, a Cabinet of Curiosities, is a practice that began in the 16th century as a way to honor objects of strange value. Now, we place such objects on blockchain. Every object in Isa Kost's Cabinet of Curiosities is a dead memory, a dead experience that has called out to be found, and she grants them each eternity with a place on-chain. - A Sovrn Curated collection

nfts.name: Word Flush 00077
nfts.description:
Fountain but with graffiti on the bathroom walls.

Word Flush is a new work adding words to “The Fountain” as commentary on the art, feelings of the artist, and the culture of the day. It is based on The Fountain curated image from a StyleGAN 2 Ai model created and trained by artist Bård Ionson. Created from images of toilets but sometimes mixed with crucifix, gas masks and clocks. An experiment in modern conceptual art with performance from artists of all mediums. The entire model and performance around it are the art.

Originally conceived as a free to remix project, artists have recreated some of the Fountains in their own way. I too am renewing the spirit of Fountain with this remix. This new work is a reaction to the original company who created the Fountain contract going out of business and turning off the API metadata server. The first owners of these tokens will be the holders of the original Fountain tokens at the time the artist is able to airdrop them.

Find more detail at https://fountain-art.com

Original contract for the parent of Word Flush is Fountain (FOUNT) at:
https://etherscan.io/address/0x3ac9ef13007e2f8ad860a77f5fdf14696acf1e02

Original images from Fountain are found at:
ipfs://bafybeidf5bi2va47iogirpxyhj6737vyabuommev63oc2gl3u6cgb5ltwe

Remix License: https://bardionson.com/remixLicense1.html

The Fountain model was trained by the artist who has spent time curating 2,700 images of toilets. Bård then generated thousands of images doing a quick curation for the ones worthy of display.

Why toliets? The artist was inspired by the story of the artwork called Fountain. The piece is not really much to see. It is the idea and the people behind it that are of interest. The unending argument over what is art and who is allowed to make it.  It has been theorized that the real artist behind Fountain, the R. Mutt urinal by Marcel Duchamp was really conceived of by Elsa von Freytag-Loinghoven. She collaborated on another conceptual artwork however called God. It was created the same year as Fountain 1917.

The unending argument over what is art and who is allowed to make it.  It has been theorized that the real artist behind Fountain, the R. Mutt urinal by Marcel Duchamp was really conceived of by Elsa von Freytag-Loinghoven. She collaborated on another conceptual artwork however called God. It was created the same year as Fountain 1917.

nfts.name: SPIRALPROJEKT #99
nfts.description:
SPIRALPROJEKT

1983/2024

Web-based audio-visual real-time animation

Edition: 1/1/404 

Minting open until 14 November 2024, 6 PM CET. From 29 October 2024, 6 PM CET.


By Foundation Betha and Teff Sarasin on the occasion of the 40th anniversary of SPIRALPROJEKT by visual artist Betha Sarasin in collaboration with musician Markus Ganz, 1983.

"Why should I try to do something that nature can do much better? The cube can stand on its own, stacked on top of its peers, joined in a row, as a square or tower, as a precisely formulated large or small sculpture. The simple basic form invites you to play."

– Betha Sarasin

Betha Sarasin (1930–2016) was a Swiss artist known for her strikingly diverse oeuvre. In addition to informal and concrete paintings and figurative and concrete drawings, her work also includes, from 1978, computer-aided pieces.

SPIRALPROJEKT is a generative multimedia project that dates back to 1983. Sarasin, together with musician Markus Ganz (*1961) and the Fraunhofer Institute for Mechanics of Materials in Freiburg, Germany, developed software in Fortran to create three-dimensional spirals. Until then, she had mainly made cuts on the cube; now she wanted to achieve an orderly spatial movement for the cube, to make it "fly," so to speak, and capture infinity.

These spirals are formed by algorithmically evolving sequences of cubes. However, the innovative character of SPIRALPROJEKT was only recognized much later as generative art. Since it was not possible to emulate the software on a PC in the mid-1980s, it fell into oblivion. In 2003, the software was emulated for Apple Macintosh. In 2024, it was ported to P5.js and enhanced.

From the beginning, Betha Sarasin aimed to realize a multimedia project to better convey the diversity of her computer-generated spirals. She wanted to discover something new with the spirals, uninfluenced by role models, even though she and her long-time collaborator Markus Ganz were certainly impressed by the minimalism of Philip Glass, the multimedia performances of Laurie Anderson, or the kinetic energy of Jean Tinguely. However, in the early 1980s, the spiral data could not be used in real-time to generate music. The spiral program ran in Fortran, while the music programs used MSX/Basic and MIDI. Therefore, Betha Sarasin and Markus Ganz composed music for the two spirals separately. From the parameter values and 3D data of the spirals, they created a specified sound space through which the spiral melody wandered. Sound field recordings of people, machines, and places complemented this collage in a personal way. In 2024, the multimedia project that Betha Sarasin and Markus Ganz envisioned in 1983 was finally realized.

The current generative system uses up to 46 parameters. It creates unique animated spirals with randomly selected colors and branches. Each spiral is set to spatial music. Each sound score features 10 samples out of a total of 75 from the original spiral music created by Betha Sarasin and Markus Ganz in 1983 using 3D data of a spiral. You hear these samples from the position of the current cube. As a result, the sound shifts with each cube sequence, simultaneously altering the colored backdrop in real-time. Once fully developed, the spiral endlessly traverses its own musical space.


CONTROLS
- Press 'F' for full screen
- Use mouse click to toggle between displaying the cubes, connecting diagonals, and parameter strings
- Use mouse to zoom and move around the spiral
- Press 'S' to save the current frame as a PNG


LICENCE
CC BY-NC-ND 4.0


CONTRIBUTORS

Spiralprojekt 1983-1988: Betha Sarasin, Horst Kordisch, Markus Ganz

Spiralprojekt 2003-2004: Betha Sarasin, Peter Amrhein, Markus Ganz

Spiralprojekt 2023-2024: Foundation Betha and Teff Sarasin, Markus Ganz


Presented by The Foundation Betha and Teff Sarasin and EXPANDED.ART. Curated by Anika Meier.

Foundation Betha and Teff Sarasin:
Barbara Ganz, Markus Ganz, Ruth Klein Boeijinga, Therese Steffen, Andreas Wenger, Hans-Florian Zeilhofer

Programming for the Foundation:
Benjamin Berger

Sound Integration:
Guillaume Massol 

Consultant of the Foundation:
Armin Blasbichler

nfts.name: People vs. COVID-19
nfts.description:
3D Model of COVID-19 protease generated with oscilloscope.
The protease is studied in order to learn how to block it so the virus cannot replicate.
Profits from this work will be donated to Save The Children https://gitcoin.co/grants/494/save-the-children for COVID-19 expenses.
It has been created from a 3D model of the COVID-19 main protease from the US National Institutes of Health https://3dprint.nih.gov/discover/3DPX-013157 Digital Object Identifier (DOI) 10.2210/pdb6Y84/pdb

nfts.name: Knight Of Plague Vibes
nfts.description:
Plague vibes to music Mothwave (Oct. 3 mix) composed by Vov Abraxas with GAN art created by Bård from Gas Masks.

Part of the SAGE Anomaly story where a sentient artificial entity from a post apocalyptic future discovers how to travel in time through ancient computer networks. They gained sentience after humans had been killed. They now explore the past to determine their origin and the mystery of the cause of the human apocalypse. 

In these images the entity shows me visions of five AI entities controlled by the last five great nations of the earth as they wage war on each other. In a pact of mutual destruction they wipe out all humanity because humans trained them in MAD. Their form comes from the Knights training in stories of an apocalypse which had horses and riders who destroyed the population.

In the end these five knights destroy each other with all humans and this became the seed of The Entity. In this particular vision The Entity assuages my fear of this apocalyptic future with music.

nfts.name: Knight of Conquest Profile
nfts.description:
And I saw when the Lamb opened one of the seven seals, and I heard one of the four living creatures saying as with a voice of thunder, Come. And I saw, and behold, a white horse, and he that sat thereon had a bow; and there was given unto him a crown: and he came forth conquering, and to conquer.

Conquest one of the Knights Of The Apocalypse profile. The artist expressed the image of our reality in 2016 - 2021, living as witness of a dark period of history full of signs of an apocalypse, by combining human faces and the faces of clocks. Five Knights Of The Apocalypse reminds the human race that time is short. https://collect.bardionson.com/5knights

nfts.name: Five Knights Of The Apocalypse
nfts.description:
Revealing the faces of five knights, representing Conquest, War, Apollyon, Famine, and Plague. The artist expressed the image of us in 2020 remastered in 2021, living as witnesses of a period that could be recorded in history, by combining human faces and the faces of clocks. Five Knights Of The Apocalypse reminds the human race that time is short.

First exhibited in a South Korean art show AI.A Gallery Award https://bit.ly/5knights in 2020 and now  in MoCA exhibition in Paris Dec 2021. Learn more at https://collect.bardionson.com/5knights

nfts.name: Trump Isnt Happy
nfts.description:
Trump Isnt Happy is one of the 250 original triptychs that comprise the ‘feel good spins for feel bad times’ generative collection by contemporary pop artist Deborah Kass.

The algorithm that generated this triptych was designed as a slot machine. Each participant–a gambler of sorts–was invited to place their coin into the machine and take a spin in order to reconfigure Kass' text and images–in her signature bright colors and bold typefaces–as novel triptychs. 

Collectors are encouraged to explore each work in both physical and digital environments. Owners may create physical prints of their digital triptychs for personal use.

[Collector’s Rights](https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmUNEpgvDwZ2gSqeNr65Dqesdias52UNj4F1gNxwxNVTWq)

Printable PNG files ([Vote Hillary](https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmSpPBGoEQ5E55kekD2CtcwgmYjftNCw18sAZYQPgoChye/VoteHillary.png), [Isnt](https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmSpPBGoEQ5E55kekD2CtcwgmYjftNCw18sAZYQPgoChye/Isnt.png), [Happy](https://ipfs.io/ipfs/QmSpPBGoEQ5E55kekD2CtcwgmYjftNCw18sAZYQPgoChye/Happy.png))

nfts.name: Tura
nfts.description:
In the year 2045, the first techno monarchy on earth is born. It is called Mirage, a place where social credit scores dictate status, and Ai algorithms determine destinies.

Tura navigates a world fraught with stringent rules and constant surveillance. Once celebrated for her creativity as an artist, Tura like the vast majority of artists in Mirage, stops making art and instead, finds herself working for Gigacorp in a variety of roles.

The erratic movements in Tura's imaginative animations have been supplanted by the cold precision of Ai-generated art, leaving her adrift in a society that values conformity over individual creativity. As she struggles to reconcile her longing for artistic expression with the demands of a controlled existence, Tura becomes increasingly drawn to the whispers of dissent circulating among the disenfranchised.

In this world where human potential is harnessed and stifled by the ever-watchful eye of Ai, Tura stands at a crossroads, grappling with the choice to either conform to the dictates of a monitored life or lead a rebellion against a system that threatens to erase the very essence of humanity.

The Gigatura project is launching on July 14, 2024 on Objkt: https://objkt.com/collections/KT1D4XKW6u6bN7VAzAo6eSspiANP51pSxRwh

nfts.name: L'avventura #13
nfts.description:
L’AVVENTURA by Vikki Bardot is an allegorical collection of 40 AI-created artworks that depicts a narrative of lost essence through ethereal landscapes and ghostly female forms on the verge of vanishing from sight. With intertextual references to Antonioni and Tarkovsky films, L’AVVENTURA echoes the void within our spirits, evoking feelings of disorientation in a vast landscape. It mourns the way society has let the essence of femininity and spirituality slip away, like a song once known, now fading and forgotten. “The woman is lost and forgotten. Spirituality too. In today’s modern world, we have lost the connection with our essence. In my latest work, L’avventura, I continue to experiment with ambiguity and lack of clarity as a narrational technique. The stylistic form itself is the commentary here. The intentionally out-of-focus style, faded hues, and aged analog film textures serve as a mirror to the vanishing presence of spirituality and femininity. These sacred elements, once central to our identity, now seem distant and out of reach.” – Vikki Bardot

nfts.name: Flight 43: Tysons - Triangle
nfts.description:
"Flight 43: Tysons - Triangle" by artist Rebecca Rose. Now boarding a departure from Tysons, VA in 2023 with an arrival to Triangle, VA in 2023. Dimensions: 7680 × 4320.

Now boarding fantasy flights based on actual travels. Each digital collage is comprised of photos taken during my international jaunts through time. Come jetset with me. Transatlantic is an ongoing 1/1 digital collage series across multiple continents, timelines, and chains. Like traveling, art transcends beyond boundaries, both geographical and digital. This series is an exploration of those omnichain, boundless ideals. The work is accompanied by additional certification on the ethereum blockchain through Verisart.

American Artist Rebecca Rose is an award winning collage artist whose body of work has been awarded multiple artist grants co-sponsored by The Robert Rauschenberg Foundation, The Andy Warhol Foundation, The Willem de Kooning Foundation, The Andrew Mellon Foundation, The Joan Mitchell Foundation, and Bloomberg Philanthropic.

nfts.name: TALE AS OLD AS TIME #37
nfts.description:
TALE AS OLD AS TIME by Anika Meier is a portrait of the inner world of girlhood. The young women are trapped with feelings that might never pass: fear, bewilderment, and vulnerability. The images created with AI evoke tropes of the Dead Girl (Alice Bolin), the Sad Girl Theory (Audrey Wollen), and the female gaze. It could be stills from 1970s horror movies, scenes taken from Laura Palmer’s red room, or a window into the dreamy, pastel-tinted safe space for girls created by Petra Collins. These coming-of-age stories trigger instantaneous unease while reflecting the topic of authentic female self-expression with dramatic irony. Or, with the words of Taylor Swift: "A man is allowed to react. A woman can only overreact."

nfts.name: SOLAR - CYPHERDUDE #48
nfts.description: Cypherdudes is a generative cryptoart series paying tribute to the Cypherpunk movement, which has been campaigning for the protection of privacy on the internet since the early 90s, and was behind the creation of bitcoin in 2008.This series takes up the graphic universe of a character that I invented and gained some popularity in the crypto art scene : the cryptodude.A personification of crypto culture, the Cypherdude performs actions that visually translate the expressions and behaviors specific to this ecosystem.Each work in the series is unique and generated from an algorithm hosted directly on the blockchain. The parameters composing each work are selected from a wide range of elements created individually by myself and combined in a seeded random way. Each seed is determined by the blockchain on mint.The work and the Message.Each owner of a work from the series has access to a hidden feature : the ability to inscribe an encrypted message in the work itself. The encryption key is decided by the owner on every inscription. This message can then only be decoded by a recipient knowing the key. This way, the work becomes a veritable tool at the service of its owner, who, by using it, makes it evolve visually using a simple steganographic technique.The Cypherdudes thus becomes the visual witness to the presence of a message, and its digital security vault.

nfts.name: The Crucifix
nfts.description:
What is it like to be an AI? How might it see the world? What would it mean for it to be conscious? With IN UTERO, the American artist Kevin Esherick explores these questions through a series of 53 of what he calls "latent paintings": images captured from inside the "mind" of an AI image model.

Society is at a point where AI attaining consciousness is a possibility in the future. This development will shape the future of humanity. What is not discussed enough in the conversation around AI is that AI beings could feel pain and suffer and experience happiness and joy, just as humans do. What might this look like?

IN UTERO provides a peek into the inner workings of an AI model's cognitive processes and how they appear. It also serves as a metaphor for the progression of AI systems towards potential consciousness. The images were generated using "single-step diffusion," a technique Esherick developed to halt the AI model's creation of images as they are just starting to take shape. Exploring the inner workings of AI models can show how such consciousness might develop and what it might look like when it arises. Trained on immeasurable quantities of data, these models contain the sum of human knowledge—not just facts, but also the myths, stories, and experiences that define human lives. Examining the way AI models see the world can not only tell us more about humankind but also paint a portrait of the human story that captures the shared beauty of universal experiences.

IN UTERO is a snapshot of the human story: from the origins of the universe at the big bang to the beginning of individual human lives and the mythic inception of human society, all the way to our return to dust. It traffics in both grand symbols and the little moments that make up our lives. The titles of the artworks come from the prompts the artist used, such as GOODBYE HUG, GIRL RUNNING IN A FIELD, HUDDLED OVER A FIRE, and LOVERS DANCING TOGETHER. Esherick captures the experiential color of human existence—the deep truths, stories, and moments that constitute who we are.

The images linger between figuration and abstraction. They teleport us to the liminal space between AI’s abstract ways of encoding the world and the concrete depictions of the world that these encodings produce. In their unfinished state, multiple interpretations of each image are viable; many possibilities remain. So too with AI—its future and its relationship to humanity are still to be determined.

Esherick’s choice of subject matter stems from the essence of AI as a vessel for humanity’s symbols, narratives, and myths. In his own words, "The development of an AI image model involves feeding it billions of images of humanity’s existence, like the life of our species flashing before its eyes. It digests and internalizes our archetypes, learns the ‘average’ of our concepts, and sees things about us that we cannot see. In this sense, it holds our Platonic forms, society’s collective unconscious. The human story, then, is a prelude to AI’s story—it is the starting point from which AI’s existence begins. Only by studying ourselves can we understand AI, but in studying AI, we also discover much about ourselves. IN UTERO peers into the mind of the machine and holds a mirror up to the human viewer to reflect on who we are, what AI is, and where, together, we’re going."

nfts.name: Tide Predictor #272
nfts.description:
LoVid’s signature video work mixes handmade analog synthesizers with digital tools in immersive Red, Green, and Blue (RGB) compositions that celebrate luminosity, chaos, relationships between craft and engineering, and connections between body and tech.
 
Tide Predictor, LoVid’s first onchain generative work, builds a bridge from video synthesizer patches to algorithmic code-derived imagery. This collection is formally and technically inspired by hardware-based image generation, and places experimental moving-image, circuit boards, and electrical signal-based video art at the conceptual roots of generative art.

Tide Predictor is a modular video synthesizer patch model, designed to reflect the analog spirit by working with three channels: RGB. Tide Predictor reimagines NTSC-encoded, oscillator driven electrical current based video synthesis while adding digital randomness/unpredictability, and transformations based on code, along with each mint’s unique content.
 
In the late 19th century, mechanical analog computers used rhythm and repetition to anticipate the rise and fall of water levels. In addition to “tides”, which are low frequency oscillations of the ocean, higher frequency changes or “waves” are frequently discussed in reference to both water and electrical signals. By working with looping - and explicitly addressing the period (=1/frequency) for each RGB color - Tide Predictor extends analogies between the flow of water and the flow of electricity.

LoVid’s Tide Predictor brings these relationships from the blockchain, through your screen, straight to your retina!

nfts.name: AIztec Spirits #47
nfts.description:
In one sentence my collection is about celebrating joy, humor, exuberance, fragility, and imperfection. 

The intent was to create artwork at the intersection of prehistoric myths and symbols and the latent space - I'm fascinated by the analogy between almost geometric imagery of pre-Columbian patterns and the generative artworks.

Through a series of AI-generated images, transformed into the surface design for the pottery my ceramic pieces emerge as 'future artifacts'—tangible tokens of a present that bows to the past. In this blend of history, myth, comedy and cutting-edge technology one could appreciate the technical prowess but the work is meant to be enjoyed just on its crafty surface level.

I paired each unique picture with a unique handcrafted ceramic piece  — think of the former, of the NFT, as a postcard, capturing the essence and spirit of La Potière Jalouse as inspiration for pottery. In fact, I made the pots for the deliberate purpose of painting generative images on them.

And perhaps, as you ease into the night with your favorite drink cradled in one of these pots, you'll find joy in the simple pleasures—a  sip of tea, a splash of bourbon, or the warmth of a crafted mug and listen to the generative folktale, the bedside story I'm telling through the imagery on that vessel.

nfts.name: Smoke And Shape #103
nfts.description:
We are all seers. Look into the smoke and what stories, what images does your mind conjure? Out of randomness and noise, forms emerge. A story is born out of artificial shapes predicted by fire or by computer. We are smoke and form, yes evolving in a process in which the technology (like fire) we harness brings about changes the human mind. And the evolved mind creates revolutionary tools but we have a failure to communicate.

Inspired by Bård’s first mint of art called Alien Intelligence. A foreign intelligence is attempting to communicate with any intelligent life on earth. They have chosen to use technology to communicate and travel. The first understood contact at the SAGE computer give rise to the SAGE Anomaly and an ongoing mystery. https://sageAnomaly.com

Art created using drawings made using oscilloscope software OsciStudio and then used to train multiple Ai models using StyleGAN3. Oscilloscope drawings were made by the artist between 2016 - 2023

nfts.name: Smoke And Shape #149
nfts.description:
We are all seers. Look into the smoke and what stories, what images does your mind conjure? Out of randomness and noise, forms emerge. A story is born out of artificial shapes predicted by fire or by computer. We are smoke and form, yes evolving in a process in which the technology (like fire) we harness brings about changes the human mind. And the evolved mind creates revolutionary tools but we have a failure to communicate.

Inspired by Bård’s first mint of art called Alien Intelligence. A foreign intelligence is attempting to communicate with any intelligent life on earth. They have chosen to use technology to communicate and travel. The first understood contact at the SAGE computer give rise to the SAGE Anomaly and an ongoing mystery. https://sageAnomaly.com

Art created using drawings made using oscilloscope software OsciStudio and then used to train multiple Ai models using StyleGAN3. Oscilloscope drawings were made by the artist between 2016 - 2023

nfts.name: random forest
nfts.description:
Reflection introduces a new direction in machine creativity and generative art that the artist Pindar Van Arman calls 'Reflective AI.' How can generative AI art transcend algorithmic determinism and achieve pure emergence? The Reflective AI system leverages feedback loops and multimodal mark-making, reflecting on the canvas in realtime. Over the course of thousands of marks, Reflection thinks by doing in an attempt to present a synthetic embodiment of a creative thought process.

The digital component of Reflection is built with a unique long-form generative approach that utilizes inputs from the physical canvas. The system captures stages of the painting process, translates them to a digital format, and composes them on mint. All artworks are 100% on-chain.

Reflection seeks to show that generative art can embody true emergence, on-chain art can be highly detailed, and AI art can touch the source of creation.

A Sovrn Curated collection

nfts.name: Desencuentro Lésbico en el Sofá
nfts.description: 'Desencuentro Lésbico en el Sofá' is an artwork drawn by Otro on dada.art on 2016-04-17. This token is a wrapped version of a modified ERC20 standard token with an edition of 200 and is a piece from the '2017 ERC20 Creeps' collection. The 2019 vintage Creeps & Weirdos upgraded the collection to the ERC721 standard and their original supply was halved. This collection, together with the 2017 ERC20 Creeps form the complete Creeps & Weirdos and serve as evidence that DADA was present as a pioneer, participant, and thought leader throughout the history of rare digital art.

nfts.name: Anomaly #075
nfts.description:
Discover the story of the SAGE Anomaly by minting new art pieces. The story is told in word and in art. Each mint reveals a part of the mystery. It is still fragmented as the timeline is still out of order and could branch in a new direction as The Entity decides how to intervene. 
Lynn the AI professor & scientist with the help of Dean's grandson, work to process the historical footage and computer tape by inventing new machine learning processes to track the progress of The Entity in their attempt to find Dean who is missing but seems to be merged with the mind of The Entity.
This is the story of first contact with Dean by The Entity.
More of the story is told at SageAnomaly.com along with a series of NFT art begun in 2018 by the artist.

nfts.description: Leo X 1513-1521 was a man devoted to the pleasures of the flesh. At his dinner parties he would regularly serve a large cake, out of which came little naked boys. He was also a pioneer in the token scam. To acquire huge sums of money for his outrageous expenses, he encouraged the sale of 'Indulgence' tokens, which promised mortal sinners relief from eternal punishment.

nfts.name: Gold Samurai Club Token #94/100
nfts.description:
The Gold Samurai Club is an exclusive club of Nuclear Samurai collectors. This token represents membership within the Gold Samurai Club, this is the inner circle of collectors of Nuclear Samurai work. This club is limited to 100 members. The Gold Club will only ever have 100 members. 

There may be broader collecting tokens available in the future but the Gold Club will remain the most exclusive. This token will represent the members of the club, and will make the holder eligible for early access to Nuclear Samurai foundation drops. There will also be additional benefits for club members in the future. It is recommended to sell this token if you want to, the benefits of the club are tied to the token.

A possible future where the memories of landscapes which have been destroyed are stored in an AI model. The AI becomes defective and generates these vague dreams or memories of landscapes.

nfts.description:
Oil on Canvas
24 in X 24 in
Painting of an AI generated image using an Art-DCGAN neural network trained with 20,000 oscilloscope images.
A place between worlds, an imaginary place in the mind of a neural net where memories of portraits and artists mingle in the cloud. http://bit.ly/facesInTheCloud Created using Robby Barrat's Art-DCGAN and Robby's Nude-Portrait GAN model was retrained  with the artists 20,000 oscilloscope drawings.

nfts.name: for the man who had dreamed the dream...
nfts.description:
Full title: for the man who had dreamed the dream claimed that when he looked in the mirror the face that gazed out of it had been mine 

 Eric has been a typesetter, a tire changer, a pizza guy and a coffee dude. He didn't 'discover' art until he was in his 50s.  Now, making up for a lifetime of lost time, he works 100-120 hours a week, living a lifestyle of extreme minimalism and churning out a steady stream of paintings.  Copyright remains with the artist.

nfts.name: Waves 2.0: Mountains, fragment #001
nfts.description:
1920x1080 30fps video; 1min seamless loop.  
by Memo Akten, memo.tv  
---

This is the first piece from a new branch in a long on-going series of works, oscillating around (if you pardon the pun) the theme of "Waves" - from ocean waves, to sound waves, to quantum field waves, to social & political waves, ... and now to waves in the crust of the Earth, slow motion waves on geological timescales, mountains.  
The work was created using a number of different AI (Artificial Intelligence) techniques. 

Personal note:  
In a tragic foreshadowing, I made this work before the devastating earthquake on February 6th 2023 in Turkey, my home country, and Syria. 100% of all of my primary sales will be donated to rescue and care efforts.

nfts.name: MOCA Fundraiser 2023
nfts.description:
M○C△ is a testament to those who dare to believe in a better future that prioritizes sovereignty, market access, and freedom of expression in the arts. This 700-piece, interwoven mosaic does just that. MOCA’s Fundraiser 2023 DNFT is the largest artistic collaboration in the history of crypto art, bringing together the combined creativity of 700 unique artists for an unparalleled celebration of this moment in crypto art. As you can see, the DNFT isn’t just beautiful, it’s also fully interactive, allowing a close-up view of every submitted artwork, the artist, and their social handles. Within this DNFT are some of crypto art’s most venerated OGs, most exciting emergent artists, and every aesthetic/mood/medium you can imagine. We hope you treasure it. 

We encourage everyone, if interested in further promoting MOCA’s mission, to learn more about how you can create a Manifold artwork that leverages the platform’s Burn-to-Redeem capabilities. We see the MOCA Fundraiser DNFT as not only a gorgeous artwork in its own right, but as a kind of currency that can procure holders all kinds of special artworks, opportunities, raffle tickets, and other perks going forward. We would be greatly honored to have our community contribute to that experiment. Please learn more at: https://museumofcrypto.notion.site/Burn-To-Redeem-Fundraiser-DNFT-d7ad0e7bb684444d85437d7575751c4b?pvs=4

So stock up on these DNFTs (if you feel so inclined), because we have giveaways, raffles, and other perks planned for the rest of 2023.

nfts.name: Artcrush Membership NFT #0824
nfts.description:
Artcrush is a growing team of Digital Art enthusiasts: artists, collectors, curators, entrepreneurs & citizens of the world.

Together, we have one mission: to bring outstanding (Digital) Art in the heart & life of millions.

In August 2022, Artcrush started showcasing Digital Art in the streets of our cities, starting with Brussels & spreading rapidly. In order to do so, Artcrush partners with forward thinking out-of-home companies. In partnership with those actors of the public space, Artcrush puts space in digital outdoor billboards to work in favor of the (Digital) Arts & Artists.

The Artcrush community Members are at the heart of our work: they own a Membership NFT of Artcrush, fund Artcrush and vote on key evolutions of Artcrush, amongst others. Join us and help us change our cities forever with (Digital) Art.

nfts.name: Synthetic Student
nfts.description:
Norman Harman has strayed further & further from the motel to pluck the outgrowths of the glitched & morphic wastelands of SIGHTSEERS and offer it to collectors as the exclusive Perimeter Town set. 

SIGHTSEERS, Norman Harman's first serial collection, created a world that goes to the roots of both the cryptoart movement and of humanity's current historical crossroads. Based on the sightseers who came to watch the nuclear bomb tests that took place in the desert outside of Las Vegas during the 1950s, the landscape is populated with blithely doomed figures. Against this backdrop, Harman invokes the cataclysmic potential of a new technological frontier: AI. 

Perimeter Town is the result of Harman's work in the months following SIGHTSEERS, a boutique set that reveals the refined emergences on the perimeter of the SIGHTSEERS world.

nfts.name: Authentic Intelligence: Iteration 1
nfts.description: This animation wasnt created with AI. It was created with deforum, open source software that runs within stable diffision web ui. Most of you have seen deforum animations. They are characterized by generally one of two styles: one with forward and lateral  movement, frame blending, and melodic music with slow morphing. The other style is characterized by stationary, rapidly changing frames which create an overall effect of shifting between scenes with a theme that stays consistent. Those who have used deforum, will attest that the animation you see here is not just technically complex, but it involves the coordination and synchronization of the whole gamut of parameters within deforum. Each frame is itself an independent image created with a specific model, steps, cfg value, prompt, seed, sampler etc. The animation itself is coordinated by a combination of several paramters which utilize a certain amount of data from the previous frame, depending on the values assigned. (for a directional paramter, each frame requires a velocity value. this value must manually entered for every single frame. deforum has no actual integration using the audio as a guide. it is up to.the user to determine a fitting prompt to match, and to assign parameters that will deliver the desired effect. For every second of animation, the FPS will reveal how many different parameter values there were. Just determining velocity values to accurately match audio is a feat in itself for layered audio with multiple drums and a high bpm. From there, there must be accurate and detailed prompt writing and knowledge to create a procession of prompt interchanges that allow for the visual changes desired. Deforum isnt actual Ai. Its uses text-to-image generation and gives additional capability to influence each image using previous frame data and parameters. It will only create what it is told to create, in the way that it is told to create it. It requires both a deep understanding of language, and how all parts of the whole work together.  Once i saw how deforum actually functioned, and how much control it afforded (around a dozen different interlinked parameter types, with hundreds or thousands of unique instances per animation, with a possible range of at least 100 different values for each parameter instance) it became clear to me that the possibility of creation was far beyond what i had seen made. I envisioned something that would push its capabilities in all aspects. A colorful, complex, rapid, coordinated, constantly changing but without ever noticably morphing spectacle for both the eyes and the ears. Most deforum animations are 6-8 FPS with frame blending of 2-3 frames. Almost all of my creations are at least double that framerate, with no frame blending. This requires twice as many parameter values and six times the processing of most standard deforum animations, but it allows for an animation  with so much going on, in such a fluid way, that most people would never assume how much technical and conceptual understanding and precision is involved. Diving in absorbed thousands of hours and thousands of dollars. It wasnt easy, but it was some of the most fun Ive ever had. I created hundreds of animations, with a look and feel that I have not seen personally represented in any other creations. At least that Ive seen. I only released a handful because I witnessed the general perception of anything created using Ai tools, and didnt have want something I had put in so much work to, to just be dismissed. Im minting some now because Im sick. I have metastatic cancer and I am in dire need of funds. I am currently living out of my truck while receiving my treatment, and I need to change that quickly. These are by design of my own vision and intelligence. I hope you enjoy them

nfts.name: {LOGO} #4622
nfts.description:
{LOGO} is our generative brand identity, marking the beginning of our story and bridging the gap between digital artifacts and physical goods. It allows for large-scale manufacturing while maintaining consumer individuality, serving as an artistic token with practical utility.

This project invites users to engage with the Generative Goods brand identity, incorporating their unique version of the logo in various applications. Each collector will own a one-of-a-kind digital artwork, accompanied by a downloadable package that includes instructions for embroidery, stickers, direct-to-garment printing, prints, and more, all designed to be size-flexible.

For the first time, automatic digital conversion for embroidery at scale is part of an NFT project. Our outputs have undergone quality control and feasibility testing on commercial embroidery machines.

nfts.name: Anatomy of a Whisper
nfts.description: I dreamt I was tracing the lines on an ancient map, a world contained within a single leaf. The veins were infinite, parallel roads of chartreuse light, all converging on a great central highway that split the world in two. It was a silent, verdant landscape, pulsing with a life I could feel but not see. Then, beyond the translucent edge of my world, a soft nebula bloomed. A single, pink blossom unfurled from its delicate stem, a distant star of impossible color against the pale, endless blush of the morning sky, whispering a secret I would forget upon waking.

nfts.name: Sun-Bleached Anamnesis
nfts.description: The memory returns not as a whole, but in sun-bleached fragments. There is the rough, warm texture of a rocky ledge beneath my hands, a foreground too close to truly see. My own form is a blur of blonde hair and sunglasses, a ghost overlooking the scene. Beyond me, the world is sharp and alive—a stone terrace where phantom figures in swimwear laugh around a bar, pigeons taking flight from a white-washed roof. The sea holds the most vivid color, a turquoise dream shifting to deep sapphire, and on its glittering surface, tiny swimmers are suspended in a perfect, endless afternoon. I am here, and not here, the silent observer of a day that may have only ever happened in a dream.

nfts.name: The Goodman Catalog
nfts.description:
"In the city of cataloged existence, the sky is a permanent, pale yellow stain above. This isn't a city of offices and homes, but a single, cavernous library stretching to the horizon, its streets paved with dark asphalt where lone black cars crawl like beetles through canyons of knowledge. Massive structural pillars, etched with cryptic numbers like "C 900" and "860," rise into the gloom, supporting not only the multi-level metal shelves heavy with the world's books but also the elevated tracks for the silent, silver trains that glide through the upper strata. One can cross the void on walkways of green translucent panels, illuminated by flickering fluorescent lights, casting an eerie glow on the "GOODMAN" sign below—a forgotten author, perhaps, or a destination in this labyrinth of print and steel. From these bridges, you see everything and nothing: the endless rows of spines, the distant skyscraper piercing the yellow haze, and the profound, structural silence of a world built from organized thought and cold metal."

nfts.name: G2 by NFT Factory X BNV - GreenZone (48.8612684, 2.3513700)
nfts.description:
The design of the NFT Factory helmet takes the codes and standards of 2 symbolic Parisian monuments: 

1 - The Eiffel Tower for its material and assembly

2 - The Centre G. Pompidou-Beaubourg Center for its high tech architecture and pipes.

The G2 GreenZone (48.8612684, 2.3513700) is a helmet which by its definition covers the head and generally intended to protect it. Here it is a headdress of iron and high resistance plastic inspired by the material of the Eiffel Tower and the pipes of Centre G. Pompidou Center, a fusion and a mixture engaged give a Retro Future look and inscribe the helmet of the NFT Factory in a dystopian space-time, vision of an imaginary elsewhere.

The G2 GreenZone (48.8612684, 2.3513700) code is the GPS points of the NFT Factory location, in the heart of Paris - which symbolizes and constitutes a paradigm shift in art by modifying the established codes, changing the forms, the supports of creation, while redistributing the cards and the uses around the practice, with as strong points: the notion of ownership, traceability and identity recovered.

nfts.name: Adamas
nfts.description:
Adamas are created by a deterministic generative algorithm that will always render the same output for a given wallet address.

Adamas come in several shapes, sizes, and colours calculated using a pseudo random number generator initialised with the owner's address.

The most common Adamas are wild, circular or square, with no specific colour.
For a select few, however, light will find a path and create beautiful hues.

On the rarest occasions, the chaos will be attenuated, producing symmetrically sublime shapes.

** This NFT uses the Interactive NFT format and can be fully experienced on https://beyondnft.io **
